= modal id: 'about', width: 500 do
	%h3 What?
	%p This search engine generates results by searching Twitter for your query and forming clusters based on similarity of the returned Tweets. From this meta data is retrieved from the most occuring URL in the cluster - this is then displayed to the user (you).
	%p Searches made are anonymously recorded for analysing the effectiveness of this system. Any feedback you have greatly appreciated; simply click the 'Not what you're looking for?' link on any results page.
	%p
		= link_to 'Continue', '#', rel: 'close'
		to the application.